[{"id":"VH932738","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram labeled “Figure 1” of a student spinning a cup that is sitting on a platform. The student holds 2 strings that are attached to opposite ends of the platform. The orientation of the platform-cup combination is drawn with the platform as vertical. The student is at the center of a horizontal dashed circle and the platform-cup combination lies on the dashed circle.\" height=\"211\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH932738.g01.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a force diagram labeled Figure 2, and consists of three arrows extending from a point. The first arrow is labeled F sub 1 and points vertically upward. The second arrow is labeled F sub 2 and points horizontally to the right. The third arrow is labeled F sub 3 and points vertically downward. The first and third arrows appear to be the same length and are longer than the second arrow.\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH932738.g02.png\" width=\"80\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student spins a cup that is in contact with a platform in a horizontal circular path at a constant speed, as shown in Figure 1. The platform is connected to two strings that are held by the student as the platform-cup system experiences uniform circular motion. A free-body diagram of the cup is shown in Figure 2. Which statement of reasoning best supports and correctly identifies the magnitude of the force the cup exerts on the platform?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH932738_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 1\"><math alttext=\"F sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because this force represents the magnitude of the force of friction between the cup and the platform.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 2\"><math alttext=\"F sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because this force represents the magnitude of the normal force exerted on the cup by the platform.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of, F sub 1 squared, plus, F sub 2 squared\"><math alttext=\"the square root of, F sub 1 squared, plus, F sub 2 squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msqrt><mrow><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></msqrt></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, because this force represents the magnitude of the total force exerted on the platform by the cup.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the square root of, F sub 1 squared, plus, F sub 2 squared, plus F sub 3 squared\"><math alttext=\"the square root of, F sub 1 squared, plus, F sub 2 squared, plus F sub 3 squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><msqrt><mrow><mstyle><mrow><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mstyle></mrow></msqrt></mrow></math></span></span>, because this represents the magnitude of the net force exerted on the cup.</p>"],"answer":2}]